10 Section 1. Chapter 5-S of Title 25 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
11 comprised of R.S. 25:380.161 through 380.166, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
12 CHAPTER 5-S. OLD GOVERNOR'S MANSION
13 §380.161. Definitions
14 For the purposes of this Chapter, the following terms shall have the meanings
15 indicated unless the context clearly provides otherwise:
16 (1) "Department" means the Department of State.
17 (2) "Secretary" means the secretary of state.
18 §380.162. Establishment and location; purpose and use
19 A. The Old Governor's Mansion is established as a facility in the City of
20 Baton Rouge under the overall jurisdiction of the department, as more specifically
21 provided in this Chapter.
22 B. The secretary shall have custody, control, and supervision of maintenance
23 of the Old Governor's Mansion and its contents. Title to the Old Governor's Mansion
24 shall remain in the state of Louisiana, along with all buildings and other
