13 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary and in particular the
14 provisions of R.S. 41:1212, the secretary may enter into contracts and agreements
15 with any public agency or nonprofit corporation which has been established for the
16 primary purpose of supporting the programs and activities of the Old Governor's
17 Mansion for the establishment of offices, stores, or exhibits on the property of and
18 in the Old Governor's Mansion. The secretary may also enter into contracts and
19 agreements for joint construction, equipment, maintenance, and financing thereof,
20 and may enter into contracts and agreements for the joint financing, supervision, and
21 conduct of cooperative enterprises and undertakings. Any public agency may enter
22 into contracts and agreements with the secretary for the purposes mentioned in this
23 Section.
24 §380.164. Operating funds
25 A. The legislature shall provide sufficient funds for the proper operation of
26 the Old Governor's Mansion.
27 B.(1) If sufficient funds necessary for the operation of the Old Governor's
28 Mansion are not appropriated by the legislature, and funds from other local, public,
29 or private sources are not available for this purpose, the department may temporarily
30 close the Old Governor's Mansion to the public until such time as sufficient funds
