14 acquired. However, the secretary shall be empowered and authorized to enter into
15 any and all contracts with any person, lender, or donor that he may deem fit, proper,
16 and necessary to accept and receive such lands, buildings, monies, relics, works of
17 art, or other property on behalf of and as additions to the Old Governor's Mansion.
18 The Old Governor's Mansion is specifically empowered to serve as the beneficiary
19 of any public trust heretofore or hereafter created for such purpose pursuant to the
20 provisions of R.S. 9:2341 through 2347.
21 B. The secretary is granted the authority of deaccession with respect to any
22 collections of the Old Governor's Mansion and for such purpose is specifically
23 exempted from the laws of the state relative to the sale or disposal of surplus
24 property. The secretary shall establish policies and procedures necessary to carry out
25 this authority in an orderly manner.
